President Cyril Ramaphosa says the sale of alcohol will be suspended with immediate effect. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says the sale of alcohol will be suspended with immediate effect. Ramaphosa made the announcement during a media briefing on Sunday. The president also said there will be a curfew from 9pm to 4am and it will take effect tomorrow. The President also announced that the country will remain on alert level 3 lockdown. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.